.TH "pm_clk_add_clk" 9 "pm_clk_add_clk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_clk_add_clk \- Start using a device clock for power management.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pm_clk_add_clk
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct clk *clk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device whose clock is going to be used for power management.
.IP "clk" 12
Clock pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add the clock to the list of clocks used for the power management of \fIdev\fP.
The power-management code will take control of the clock reference, so
callers should not call \fBclk_put\fP on \fIclk\fP after this function sucessfully
returned.
